<div type="definition">
<p>COMPLEX ORDERLY SHAPE of something.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The general word for a pattern is wén 文.</p>
<p>2. Zhāng 章 is specifically a conspicuous pattern in red and white.</p>
<p>3. Lǐ 理 refers to patterns inherent in things.</p>
        </div>
